<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph>Annotations can be added to any point in a chart.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Annotation placement in a chart can be controlled using the <Bold>OffsetX</Bold> and <Bold>OffsetY</Bold> properties.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>


<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>


<List Margin="25,0,0,0">

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Slider <Bold>"Offset X"</Bold> controls the position of the ChartAnnotationLabel with respect to a particular x-axis value. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Slider <Bold>"Offset Y"</Bold> controls the position of the ChartAnnotationLabel with respect to a particular y-axis value. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Description"</Bold> helps in changing the description of the annotation.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Template"</Bold> helps in changing the templates for the annotation label.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Annotation Shapes"</Bold> helps in changing the annotation shapes for annotation label.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Fill"</Bold> helps in changing the annotation interier for annotation label.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The check box <Bold>"Enable Context Menu"</Bold> helps to enable ContextMenu to add Annotations dynamically.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The check box <Bold>"Enable Drag Drop"</Bold> helps to enable Drag and Drop for Chart annotations.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Intersect Action"</Bold> helps to set Intersect Action for the overlapped annotations.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
</List>
</FlowDocument>